    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "The problem is the reporter from the Chronicle already knows there wasn't a compromise. They're going to say we're just caving to party leadership behind closed doors. If we use the 'compromise' line, they'll call us liars. How do we spin this so it doesn't look like they just changed their mind because they were told to?",
