      "content": "That's a stretch. There wasn't any \"thorough review\" or new data. The candidate literally just got a call from the whip and was told to fall in line or face a primary challenge. If we claim they did a deep dive into the provisions when they didn't actually read the updated version, and a reporter gets hold of the meeting logs, we're cooked. Is there a way to spin this without making up fake technical reviews?",
